727413f-a.text:
Metropolitan Avenue, (foreground, tracks thereon), between Flushing Avenue (left) and 53rd Street (right, not shown), showing at the right rear views of homes on the last mentioned Street. At the left is a small home on the north side of the second mentioned Avenue. At the intersection of the aforementioned Avenues, in 1852, stood a tollgate. This area was once known, as Oceanville. This is a set of two views.
1922
Views 1 and 2
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
